Table dimensions

Source: R/tree_accessors.R
dimensions.Rd

Table dimensions

Usage

# S4 method for class 'VTableTree'
nrow(x)

# S4 method for class 'VTableNodeInfo'
ncol(x)

# S4 method for class 'VTableNodeInfo'
dim(x)

Arguments

x

(TableTree or ElementaryTable)
a table object.

Value

The number of rows (nrow), columns (ncol), or both (dim) of the object.

Examples

lyt <- basic_table() %>%
  split_cols_by("ARM") %>%
  analyze(c("SEX", "AGE"))

tbl <- build_table(lyt, ex_adsl)

dim(tbl)
#> [1] 7 3
nrow(tbl)
#> [1] 7
ncol(tbl)
#> [1] 3

NROW(tbl)
#> [1] 7
NCOL(tbl)
#> [1] 3
